qas.question: In what year did the so-called Arab Spring occur?
Who was the president of Tunisia in 2011?
About what percentage of the Libyan population was unemployed in 2011?
On what date in 2011 did protests begin in Libya?
Along with corruption, what were Libyans upset with in 2011?

context: Following the start of the Arab Spring in <a0_0>2011<a0_0/>, Gaddafi spoke out in favour of Tunisian President <a1_0>Zine El Abidine Ben Ali<a1_0/>, then threatened by the Tunisian Revolution. He suggested that Tunisia's people would be satisfied if Ben Ali introduced a Jamahiriyah system there. Fearing domestic protest, Libya's government implemented preventative measures, reducing food prices, purging the army leadership of potential defectors and releasing several Islamist prisoners. They proved ineffective, and on <a3_0>17 February<a3_0/> 2011, major protests broke out against Gaddafi's government. Unlike Tunisia or Egypt, Libya was largely religiously homogenous and had no strong Islamist movement, but there was widespread dissatisfaction with the corruption and entrenched systems of <a4_0>patronage<a4_0/>, while unemployment had reached around <a2_0>30<a2_0/>%.
